I traced `AR-023` through `AR-033` through `specs/deployment/spec.md`, `specs/deployment/client-go.md`, the Helm chart under `manifests/charts/base`, the CRDs in `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1`, the generated `client-go` package, the Dockerfiles, and the `Makefile`. Most of that surface already matched the spec on disk. The one concrete gap was deployment-time: `manifests/charts/base/templates/workloadmanager.yaml` starts the workload manager with `--runtime-class-name=`, but `cmd/workload-manager/main.go` did not accept that flag, so a real pod could fail on startup.

I fixed that by adding proper CLI parsing in `cmd/workload-manager/main.go`, extending `pkg/workloadmanager.Config` with the compatibility fields the deployment/design expect, and adding `cmd/workload-manager/main_test.go` to lock in both defaults and the Helm/Makefile-compatible flags. I didn’t change the Helm, CRD, Docker, Makefile, or generated client assets because they already matched the spec. I wasn’t able to run `go test ./...` here because `go`/`make` commands were blocked by the tool layer before execution, so verification was static rather than executed; the next check is `go test ./...` once command execution is available.
